<dcterms:description xml:lang="en">This dataset consists of weekly mean sizes of Perch (Perca fluviatilis) from trapping at Green Tuft, Windermere, Cumbria, sampled between 1946 and 2012.  Perch have been monitored in the north and south basins of Windermere by trapping with variations in sampling sites and efforts from 1943 to the present.  The data were initially collected by the Freshwater Biological Association (FBA) but have been collected by the Centre for Ecology & Hydrology (CEH) and its predecessor Institute of Freshwater Ecology (IFE) since 1989.   </dcterms:description>         <documentcontainer:id xml:lang="en">495fd597-42b2-4985-96dc-3d9ec024b829</documentcontainer:id>       </documentcontainer:documentContainer>     </dcterms:isPartOf>     <dcterms:modified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2014-08-11T15:02:33Z</dcterms:modified>     <file:id xml:lang="en">perch-weekly-mean-sizes-from-green-tuft-1946-2012-dataset-documentation</file:id>     <dcterms:title xml:lang="en">Perch weekly mean sizes from Green Tuft 1946-2012 Dataset Documentation</dcterms:title>   </file:File> </rdf:RDF>
